race.comment: Going with the promising WICKED STORM (13) who returns from a long break. Too good on debut, ran well in town then safely held last run before another break. Fitter for four jump-outs and expected to measure up this level. SHELLY'S LEGACY (8) stood flat footed at the start last time, gave away all hope and finished at the tail. Much better than that and can atone. NEPELA (15) wasn't far away last time and is edging towards a win, the latest effort a solid third over 1100m at this track. Among the leading chances. EL SALTO (2) made late ground last time but found one better over 1000m at Tatura, beaten only a head. Veteran who can feature on his day and could be overs from the wide gate. MR TICKLES (1) bounced back last start and landed the prize by a neck over 1000m at Moe. Drawn to be prominent and looks hard to beat again.
